# LLM Monitoring Capstone

MasterFabric Academy base case: **Raw LLM Monitoring + Deci.Scoring**.

## Architecture

- Monorepo: `frontend/` (Next.js SPA → Vercel), `backend/` (Go + Postgres → Render)
- Inference is **browser-only** via `@mlc-ai/web-llm` (Gemma). Backend never calls a model.
- Backend records raw runs, scores them, serves auth/config/metrics.

## Assignment checklist

- Next.js SPA, ≥3 master views (Auth + Playground + Monitoring), auth subviews
- Web MLC-LLM + Gemma keyword path
- Go API ≥20 endpoints: Config[2] + Auth[8+] + WEB MLC-LLM[6–8] + Common
- Live deploys: Vercel FE + Render BE
- MCP workflow: Render + Vercel + MF Academy

## Do / Don't

- DO keep scoring rule-based and transparent (breakdown + rationale)
- DO scope all LLM data per authenticated user
- DON'T add server-side LLM proxy as the primary path
- DON'T invent endpoints outside Config/Auth/LLM/Common without updating README
- Prefer patterns from the reference repo structure over greenfield redesigns
